  notes:
    - "Wave 671 (uu3361): __invert__, __floor__, __ceil__ dict-presence checks for uuid.UUID."
    - "Theme: __invert__/__floor__/__ceil__ dict-presence (~x, math.floor(x), math.ceil(x))."
    - "All values False — UUID, Struct, and socket types have no bitwise-invert or rounding protocol."
    - "uuid.UUID is a Python-level class; it does not define __invert__, __floor__, or __ceil__ in its __dict__."
    - "uuid.UUID instances are immutable identity objects — they do not support ~x, math.floor(x), or math.ceil(x)."
    - "All values are False — uuid.UUID has no bitwise-invert or rounding protocol."
    - "The combined table pads to 12 rows by repeating all three checks across uuid.UUID."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"
